    <tags>pdf viewer editor annotate merge split sign portable</tags>
    <summary>PDF editor for Windows. No Adobe, no subscription, no telemetry.</summary>
    <description>PDF editor for Windows. View, annotate, merge, split, edit text, draw, sign, print, flatten, and open password-protected PDFs without an Adobe subscription or a phone-home.

**Features:**

- High-quality rendering via PDFium
- Merge multiple PDFs and split out selected pages, drag-and-drop page reordering
- Inline text editing with font matching against the original document
- Text boxes, freehand drawing, and highlight overlays
- PDF form filling: text inputs, checkboxes, and radio buttons render as live controls
- PDF outline (bookmark) navigation: OUTLINES tab displays the bookmark tree
- Draw and save reusable signatures or import a PNG/JPG/BMP image
- Insert images as resizable annotations
- Crop tool with corner drag handles
- Right-click sidebar: insert blank page, rotate, move, extract, or delete
- Clickable PDF links and internal cross-references
- Full-text search across the entire document with result highlighting
- Keyboard shortcut overlay (Ctrl+?)
- Single Windows EXE, ~6 MB, no runtime install required
- GPLv3, local-only, no account, no telemetry
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/YOUR-GH-USER/Scalpel/releases/tag/vREPLACE_VERSION</releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="tools\**" target="tools" />
  </files>
</package>
